@Node Register "DLManager Registration"
@{b}@{u}DLManager Registration@{ub}@{uu}

DLManager is Shareware, I would like you to at least send me an EMail
saying you are using it.  If you do use it on a regular basis please tell
me so.

When you have EMailed me - telling me you are using it - you will be put
on a "list" (if you want) of 'unlimited' free updates to the script.  You
will also get free support, and a clear conscience.
@EndNode

@Node Installation "DLManager Install Guide"
@{b}@{u}DLManager Installation@{ub}@{uu}

*********************************************************
**   Library Files needed:			       **
**	     bbsread.library (of course)	       **
**	     rexxarplib.library (get it from Aminet!)  **
**	     rexxsupport.library (get it from Aminet!) **
*********************************************************

Installation is easy and painless!  Just copy DLManager.thor to
your [VOLUME]:Thor/rexx directory and run it!

When you run DLManager a window will appear with eight (08) buttons.
Those buttons are:
   1) Get System
   2) New/Add List
   3) WriteMesg
   4) DelList
   5) Quit
   6) Edit DisList
   7) About
   8) Delete User (single)

They perform the following functions (in order of appearance):
1.  Get System	 - gets the system you want to send the email from.
		   Also used for getting email address from the
		   User Database.

2.  New/Add List - Creates a list or adds to an existing list.
		   can add the address manually or from the
		   User Database.

3.  WriteMesg	 - Get Ready to write your message!  This also adds the
		   message as an event.  Uses your configured editor.

4.  DelList	 - Deletes the list you select (use Caution!)

5.  Quit	 - Ends the program.

6.  Edit DisList - Edits a list you select.  If you don't want to use Nr. 2
		   above use this to add/delete the email addresses.
		   Used mostly for deleting multiple email addresses.

7.  About	 - About

8. Delete User	 - Deletes a user from a .tdl file.  It only deletes
		   one user at a time - even though you select many
		   - Sorry but this is the best I can do right now
		   my programing skills aren't that good yet.
@EndNode

