@Node History "DLManager History"
@{b}@{u}DLManager History@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}	     v1.1 - First Release!  - (12.04.97)@{ub}

@{b}	     v1.2 - Second Release!  - (12.06.97)@{ub}
		    Fixed a bug that caused DLManager to crash
		    when adding addresses to a new distribution list.

		    Fixed a second bug that cropped up when I
		    fixed the first bug!  The Delete command
		    (button) didn't work until you selected
		    New/Add or Edit.  Sheesh!

@{b}	     v1.3 - Third Release!  - (12.07.97)@{ub}
		    This is really an "upgrade" I guess.  I added
		    a function that will allow your .sig file to
		    be added to your outgoing messages.

@{b}	     v1.4 - Fourth Release! - (12.26.97)@{ub}
		    Rewrote the Add user function.  The users are
		    now on their own lines and if you have more
		    than 250 characters in the file, DLManager will
		    break it up and add Cc: headers.  This routine
		    was shamlessly stripped from BulkMail!  Suitably
		    changed of course to make it work for DLManager!

@{b}	     v1.5 - Fifth Release! - (03JAN98)@{ub}
		    Rewrote the write message function and added
		    a WriteCC() function.  You can now have as many
		    users in a .tdl file as you want.

		    DLManager will search the .tdl file until it reaches
		    > 250 characters, when it does it adds a new line
		    and appends a 'Cc:' to the header of your outgoing
		    message and adds the rest of the addresses there.

@{b}	     v1.7 - Seventh Release - (31MAR98) (really sixth)@{ub}
		    Added a function that will add the sig files @{b}and@{ub}
		    change the $ver and $time keywords that Thor uses.
		    This is an update I guess you could say to v1.3
@EndNode
